goodbye i wrote this after the man i thought i was going to spend the rest of my life with sent me a text message telling me he let a girl move in with him and he wasn't sure if things between us would work we lived in different cities it s been a long time coming goodbye is the hardest word to say but it is something i must do i just wish i could say it to your face you have broken every promise left my heart broken and tattered i love you all that you would say as if that were all that mattered i still want you heart and soul but only if you are mine alone please don t try to hold onto me now for your love for me is gone i'm making a book of my poetry and not sure if i want to include this one what do you think should i put it in or just keep it in a notebook i would put it in your book because it has meaning for alot of people and they might get the same thing out of it as you did putting it in it is beautiful and came from your heart and to me thats true poetry something heart felt not something just wrote on paper let others read and share your heart felt words because it is beautifully toughing and should be in your book for everyone to read words from the heart should not be hiddin Jon Secada The Amber Spyglass Time Out of Mind One Tree Hill (TV series) The Beatles discography Anne Rice Socrates Friends Blood on the Tracks Cliff Richard W.I.T.C.H. Spice Girls Book of Mormon Social rule Simone Weil Yehuda Halevi The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan Book of Isaiah Max Martin Current teachings of Prem Rawat Eli Siegel The Isley Brothers Ludwig Wittgenstein Love Paul Is Dead Kurt Cobain The McGuire Sisters Literature The Catcher in the Rye Pitaten Humphrey Bogart John the Baptist Gary Snyder Past teachings of Prem Rawat W. Daniel Hillis Bonnie Tyler Anglo-Saxon literature Theory of conduct Miss Saigon Novel Emanuel Swedenborg Poetry Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Jack Kerouac Jeremiah Sabbath Discordianism Bushido Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Unrelease